Here's a complete example for your `mymodule/src/Drush/Commands/NodeCommands.php` file:

```php
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace Drupal\mymodule\Drush\Commands;

use Drupal\Core\Entity\EntityTypeManagerInterface;
use Drush\Attributes as CLI;
use Drush\Commands\DrushCommands;
use Symfony\Component\DependencyInjection\ContainerInterface;

/**
 * Drush commands for node operations.
 */
class NodeCommands extends DrushCommands {

  protected EntityTypeManagerInterface $entityTypeManager;

  public function __construct(EntityTypeManagerInterface $entityTypeManager) {
    $this->entityTypeManager = $entityTypeManager;
  }

  /**
   * {@inheritdoc}
   */
  public static function create(ContainerInterface $container): self {
    return new static($container->get('entity_type.manager'));
  }

  /**
   * List published nodes of a given bundle.
   */
  #[CLI\Command(name: 'node:list', aliases: ['nlist'])]
  #[CLI\Argument(name: 'bundle', description: 'Node bundle machine name (e.g., article)')]
  #[CLI\Option(name: 'limit', description: 'Maximum number of nodes to list', valueRequired: false, default: 10)]
  public function listNodes(string $bundle, array $options = ['limit' => 10]): void {
    $query = $this->entityTypeManager->getStorage('node')->getQuery();
    $query->condition('status', 1)
      ->condition('type', $bundle)
      ->range(0, $options['limit'])
      ->sort('created', 'DESC');

    $nids = $query->execute();

    if (empty($nids)) {
      $this->io()->warning("No published nodes found for bundle '$bundle'.");
      return;
    }

    $nodes = $this->entityTypeManager->getStorage('node')->loadMultiple($nids);
    $rows = [];

    foreach ($nodes as $node) {
      $rows[] = [
        'nid' => $node->id(),
        'title' => $node->label(),
        'changed' => $node->getChangedTime()->format('Y-m-d H:i:s'),
      ];
    }

    $this->io()->table(['nid', 'title', 'changed'], $rows);
    $this->io()->success("Listed " . count($rows) . " published nodes of type '$bundle'.");
  }
}
```

Key points:
- Extend `DrushCommands`
- Use `#[CLI\Command]`, `#[CLI\Argument]`, `#[CLI\Option]` (no docblock annotations)
- Inject `EntityTypeManagerInterface` via constructor + `create()` factory
- Use `$this->io()->success()` / `$this->io()->table()` for output

